  <tr>
    <td align="left" valign="top" class="p_align"><p>Our DSS dentists are committed to our high standards and rigid protocols for treatment.  If you have a patient that you would like to refer to one of our offices we will be happy to see them for a free consultation to evaluate if they are a good candidate for Dental Device Therapy.  Throughout their treatment you will be part of the process and will be kept informed of your patient’s progress.  During the process you will be given multiple written updates to help you track your patient’s success.  This written correspondence will not only keep you informed, it will serve as the proper medical documentation needed to defer your liability for untreated Obstructive Sleep Apnea patients.</p><ol start="1" type="1" id="ol_sty">
  <li>Call or email us with the prospective patient’s name, address and phone number. Once we have contacted the patient you will receive a <u>thank you letter</u> to let you know that we have the patient scheduled for an appointment.</li>
  <li><strong>Free Patient Consultation</strong> – Your patient will be evaluated as to whether they are a good candidate for Dental Sleep Therapy. Other treatment alternatives will also be discussed including CPAP and surgery. – A <u>letter will be sent</u> to all of the patient’s medical providers even if they are not a candidate for treatment or if they choose not to complete       treatment.</li>
  <li><strong>Examination, Records and Impressions- </strong>During the second appointment your patient will receive a complete oral and airway examination and impressions will be taken for their dental sleep device.</li>
  <li><strong>Delivery of Dental Sleep Device </strong>–The third appointment will consist of delivering of the patient’s dental       sleep device along with instructions for use. After this appointment a <u>comprehensive letter</u> will be sent to all of the patient’s medical providers, as well as the patient, detailing our findings and procedures. </li>
  <li><strong>Follow up Subjective Evaluation appointments </strong>– Multiple appointments will be completed post device       placement to evaluate and titrate the patient’s subjective relief of symptoms.</li>
  <li><strong>Portable Sleep Test </strong>– The patients will be fitted with a level 3 home sleep recorder to evaluate the sleep       device effectiveness.  It may be necessary to repeat this study multiple times in order to achieve maximum medical       improvement with their dental sleep device.</li>
  <li><strong>Patient Dismissal </strong>– Once the patient has achieved the maximum medical improvement, all of their medical       providers will be provided with a<u> letter stating the results of treatment.</u>  A copy of the portable sleep test will be provided to their sleep physician along with a recommendation for a follow –up dental device PSG.</li>
  <li><strong>Yearly Recall</strong> – The patients are requested to return annually for an evaluation of their dental sleep       device. - All of their medical providers will receive a <u>letter</u> summarizing the findings of this visit</li>
</ol></td>
